This is because the check for bucket names that do not map to a valid DNS name is applied indiscriminately in DbBucketManagerImpl:checkBucketName

		if(!bucketName.matches("^[A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9._-]+"))
			return false;

AWS only enforces this in non US regions.

EUCA-6208 added a property to allow the desired behaviour to be specified for Walrus:

{code}
walrus.bucketnamesrequirednscompliance = false
{code}
